      </aside>
      <article class="legal-body">
        <section>
              <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>
              <p>This Privacy Policy explains how Clearline Capital LLC collects, uses, discloses, retains, and protects information submitted through this public website and related communications.</p>
              <p>This website is intended for business and professional use. Please do not submit confidential, proprietary, regulated, or sensitive personal information unless a separate written confidentiality agreement is in place.</p>
              </section>
            <section>
              <h2 id="information-clearline-capital-llc-collects">Information Clearline Capital LLC collects</h2>
              <p>Clearline Capital LLC may collect the following categories of information through the Access request process and related communications:</p>
              <ul>
              <li>Full name.</li>
              <li>Phone number.</li>
              <li>Email address.</li>
              <li>Referring party or referred-by information.</li>
              <li>Optional LinkedIn, Instagram, or X profile information submitted by the visitor.</li>
              <li>Context supplied with the Access request.</li>
              <li>Invitation-code, token, and token-validation information associated with the Access request.</li>
              <li>Legal acceptance records associated with the Access request, including acceptance value, policy-version identifiers, effective dates, and a submission timestamp.</li>
              <li>Technical and security information associated with website access, token-validation flows, or form submission, including IP address, browser information, timestamps, request paths, server logs, and security metadata.</li>
              <li>Communications and related business records if Clearline Capital LLC communicates with you after a submission.</li>
              </ul>
              <p>Clearline Capital LLC does not ask visitors to submit confidential, proprietary, regulated, or sensitive personal information through the public Access form unless a separate written confidentiality agreement is in place.</p>
              </section>
            <section>
              <h2 id="website-services-and-providers">Website services and providers</h2>
              <p>Clearline Capital LLC uses Netlify for website hosting and serverless functions that support the public website and Access process. Clearline Capital LLC uses Google Workspace for domain email. This website uses Google Fonts for font delivery.</p>
              <p>When these services operate, they may process technical information necessary to provide, secure, route, transmit, or support the website, email, font delivery, token-validation flows, and Access request process.</p>
              <p>Clearline Capital LLC does not currently use analytics tools, advertising pixels, first-party cookies, or automatic AI processing of Access submissions as part of the public Access form workflow.</p>
              </section>
            <section>
              <h2 id="how-clearline-capital-llc-uses-information">How Clearline Capital LLC uses information</h2>
              <p>Clearline Capital LLC may use information to:</p>
              <ul>
              <li>Operate, maintain, secure, and improve the website and Access request process.</li>
              <li>Receive, route, review, and respond to Access requests, introductions, referrals, and opportunity submissions.</li>
              <li>Validate, route, and administer invitation-code and token-related Access flows.</li>
              <li>Evaluate whether to pursue discussions, diligence, introductions, or business opportunities.</li>
              <li>Manage communications, records, workflow, compliance, and internal review.</li>
              <li>Maintain legal acceptance records for the Privacy Policy, Terms of Use, and Submission Terms.</li>
              <li>Protect Clearline Capital LLC, its website, systems, business operations, and legal rights.</li>
              <li>Comply with legal obligations, lawful requests, and applicable process.</li>
              </ul>
              </section>
            <section>
              <h2 id="analytical-and-ai-assisted-review">Analytical and AI-assisted review</h2>
              <p>Clearline Capital LLC maintains separate internal business, market-intelligence, and analytical capabilities. The public Access form is not automatically integrated with Clearline Capital LLC&#x27;s internal agentic platform.</p>
              <p>Authorized Clearline Capital LLC personnel may use approved analytical or AI-assisted tools to help organize, summarize, classify, or evaluate submitted information and related communications. Any such use is subject to human review, access controls, applicable provider terms, and Clearline Capital LLC policy. Use of these tools does not create an approval, commitment, compensation right, exclusivity, confidentiality obligation, or obligation for Clearline Capital LLC to respond or proceed.</p>
              </section>
            <section>
              <h2 id="how-clearline-capital-llc-discloses-information">How Clearline Capital LLC discloses information</h2>
              <p>Clearline Capital LLC may disclose information only as appropriate for the following purposes:</p>
              <ul>
              <li>Service providers that technically process, host, transmit, store, secure, route, or support information for Clearline Capital LLC, including website hosting, serverless-function, form-processing, email, font-delivery, security, and related support providers.</li>
              <li>Professional legal, compliance, accounting, or similar advisors when legitimately necessary.</li>
              <li>Legal, regulatory, law-enforcement, court, or governmental requests, obligations, or proceedings.</li>
              <li>Corporate succession transactions, such as a merger, restructuring, transfer, financing, sale, acquisition, or similar transaction involving Clearline Capital LLC or relevant assets, where legally appropriate.</li>
              </ul>
              <p>Clearline Capital LLC does not create a relationship, transaction commitment, exclusivity, compensation right, or obligation to respond or proceed merely because information is submitted through the website.</p>
              </section>
            <section>
              <h2 id="retention">Retention</h2>
              <p>Clearline Capital LLC retains website, Access request, legal acceptance, technical, security, communication, and related business records for as long as reasonably necessary for the purposes described in this Privacy Policy, including business review, relationship management, security, troubleshooting, compliance, legal, tax, accounting, dispute-resolution, audit, and recordkeeping purposes.</p>
              <p>Retention periods may vary depending on the type of record, the status of the related opportunity or communication, legal or contractual obligations, system capabilities, security needs, backup practices, and whether a legal hold, investigation, dispute, audit, or legally required preservation obligation applies.</p>
              <p>When information is no longer reasonably needed, Clearline Capital LLC may delete, archive, de-identify, or minimize it using commercially reasonable methods appropriate to the record type and system involved. Deletion from active systems may not immediately remove residual copies from provider logs, archives, backups, security records, or systems controlled by service providers.</p>
              </section>
            <section>
              <h2 id="security">Security</h2>
              <p>Clearline Capital LLC uses reasonable administrative, technical, and organizational measures intended to protect information. No website, email system, storage system, serverless-function workflow, form-processing workflow, or transmission method is completely secure.</p>
              </section>
            <section>
              <h2 id="privacy-contact">Privacy contact</h2>
              <p>Privacy questions or requests may be sent to info@clearlinecapital.co.</p>
            </section>
      </article>
